**Duplicate middleware `Name` silently produces inconsistent pipeline output**

`RenderPluginConfig` was fixed in this PR to return an error when two `PluginSpec` entries share the same `ConfigSection`. `RenderPastePipeline` has an analogous gap: if two `MiddlewareSpec` entries in `spec.Middleware` share the same `Name` but have different positions or configs, the loop at line 69 overwrites `result[filterSection]` on the second iteration, while both name tokens were already appended to `beforeFilters`/`afterFilters` in the earlier loop. The resulting output is:

- Pipeline directive: `"audit cors audit service_v3"` — the name appears twice
- Filter section: only the **second** entry's factory/config is emitted

This means the first "audit" token in the pipeline references a section that was defined by the second entry's config — silently wrong.

Consider adding a duplicate-name guard consistent with `RenderPluginConfig`:

```go
seen := make(map[string]struct{}, len(spec.Middleware))
for _, mw := range validMiddleware {
    if _, exists := seen[mw.Name]; exists {
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("duplicate middleware Name %q in pipeline %q", mw.Name, spec.PipelineName)
    }
    seen[mw.Name] = struct{}{}
    // ... rest of filter section generation
}
```

(Note: this would require `RenderPastePipeline` to return `(map[string]map[string]string, error)`, mirroring `RenderPluginConfig`.)
